Reason: partial-operation contracts require exactly 2 argument(s); under-applied or over-applied partial operations must use a proof-carrying function-wrapper design before they can be emitted soundly

This is a deliberate translator-level rejection — the Lean backend doesn't have a sound
transposition for this primitive yet. If your Cryptol code specialised down to it,
